# Go Test Style

- Use the standard `testing` package with `github.com/stretchr/testify/assert`.
- Keep tests in the same package unless external-package tests are clearly needed.
- Prefer table-driven tests when covering multiple input or error cases.
- Cover both happy paths and representative failure paths for public behavior.
- Keep fixtures small and inline when possible so tests stay easy to scan.
- When test data resembles a secret or token, add `// gitleaks:allow` on the relevant line.
- Prefer clear assertions over helper-heavy abstractions.
- Match the repository's naming style: `TestXxx`, with `t.Run(...)` for subcases when it improves readability.
